Dia. 04 Value of Reverse Sente
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Let's check Black's hane and connection with 1 and 3.
\par It was said that Black's hane and connection is gote, wasn't it?
\par Therefore Black 1 and 3 is \cf1\b 3 points gote endgame\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par This gote endgame which provides the opponent to play sente endgame is on a different level from the simple gote endgame. This kind of endgame is called \cf1\b reverse sente\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par The value of reverse sente is double. Therefore Black 1 and 3 is not 3, but 6 points.
\par
\par }
